    {
      "title": "Nouns of Place and Time (أسماء المكان والزمان)",
      "titleArabic": "أسماء المكان والزمان",
      "content": [
        "Nouns of place and time indicate where or when an action takes place. They are derived from verbs using specific patterns depending on the verb type."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern مَفْعَل is used when the middle radical has fathah or dammah",
        "Pattern مَفْعِل is used when the middle radical has kasrah",
        "These nouns indicate location or time of the verbal action"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "مَكْتَب", "english": "office / desk (place of writing)" },
        { "arabic": "مَطْبَخ", "english": "kitchen (place of cooking)" },
        { "arabic": "مَوْعِد", "english": "appointment / time of promise" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "Form VI Verbs (تَفَاعَلَ)",
      "titleArabic": "باب تَفَاعَلَ",
      "content": [
        "Form VI verbs are formed by prefixing تَ to Form III. This pattern typically indicates reciprocal action between two or more parties, or pretending to do an action."
      ],
      "keyPoints": [
        "Pattern: تَفَاعَلَ (tafā'ala) - prefix tā' to Form III",
        "Maṣdar pattern: تَفَاعُل (tafā'ul)",
        "Indicates mutual/reciprocal action between parties",
        "Can indicate pretending: تَمَارَضَ (to pretend to be sick)"
      ],
      "examples": [
        { "arabic": "تَبَادَلَ", "english": "to exchange (with each other)" },
        { "arabic": "تَعَاوَنَ", "english": "to cooperate" },
        { "arabic": "تَسَاءَلَ", "english": "to wonder / ask oneself" }
      ]
    }
  ],
